<div id="review_1652937864" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1652937864" />
    <a title="Pei-jean Lu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11087057-pei-jean-lu"><img alt="Pei-jean Lu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1407755297p2/11087057.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1652937864?book_show_action=true">Oct 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pei-jean Lu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pei-jean Lu" href="/user/show/11087057-pei-jean-lu">Pei-jean Lu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8152840-easy-company-soldier">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1652937864&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1652937864" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4311313087170880221">Sgt Donald Malarkey was one of many young men whose life would be forever shaped by the turmoil of WWII. A member of the famed Band of Brothers, he would serve on the front line for most of his service. <br/>Mixing with his happy go lucky outlook on life is his honesty about his survivors guilt as he recounts the various episodes that in reality should have gotten him killed or the moments when he encountered the realities of war. The two most poignant of which are shown in the miniseries where he en</span>
  <span id="freeText4311313087170880221" style="display:none">Sgt Donald Malarkey was one of many young men whose life would be forever shaped by the turmoil of WWII. A member of the famed Band of Brothers, he would serve on the front line for most of his service. <br />Mixing with his happy go lucky outlook on life is his honesty about his survivors guilt as he recounts the various episodes that in reality should have gotten him killed or the moments when he encountered the realities of war. The two most poignant of which are shown in the miniseries where he encounters a young soldier who is fighting for the Germans who worked across the street from a factory he’d been working at prior to his enlistment (and who also was born in a town not far from his hometown). The other is when he goes to collect his laundry and realises that many of his comrades had been killed or were considered MIA.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4311313087170880221" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


